name: NADH dehydrogenase
reaction: NADH + H+ + acceptor = NAD+ + reduced acceptor [RN:R00281]
comment: A flavoprotein containing iron-sulfur centres. After preparations have been subjected to certain treatments, cytochrome c may act as an acceptor. Under normal conditions, two protons are extruded from the cytoplasm or the intramitochondrial or stromal compartment. Present in a mitochondrial complex as EC 1.6.5.3, NADH dehydrogenase (ubiquinone).
